                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-10-19</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This book is very suitable for those who want to establish entrepreneurship without any experience before. Since there are lots of marketing ideas, which are different from the common practices of other companies. The ideas the author recommended are very fruitful such as, how to build up a professional look for yourself, have a good image for your company, how to impress the press to report your success. The marketing ideas will not consume high cost, but they are creative enough for you to promote your product and company. The idea i treasure most is referal, it is a low cost promotion method which only require customer relationship with word-of-mouth communication.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Practical and meaningful</div>
